MethodDeclaration * Resolves all forward references to this This method must be * when this label is added to the bytecode of the method, i.e. when * position becomes known. This method fills in the blanks that where left * the bytecode by forward reference previously added to this * @param owner the code writer that calls this * @param position the position of this label in the * @param data the bytecode of the * @return if a that was left for this label was to * to store the offset. In such a case the corresponding jump * is replaced with a pseudo instruction (using unused opcodes) using * unsigned two bytes offset. These pseudo instructions will need to * replaced with true instructions with wider offsets (4 bytes instead * 2). MethodDeclaration * Resizes the designated instructions, while keeping jump offsets * instruction addresses consistent. This may require to resize other * instructions, or even to introduce new for * increasing the size of an instruction by 2 at the of a method * increases the offset of an IFEQ instruction from 32766 to 32768, in * case IFEQ 32766 must be replaced with IFNEQ 8 GOTO_W 32765. This, in * may require to increase the size of another jump instruction, and so * All these operations are handled automatically by this * * <i>This method must be called after all the method that is being built * been visited</i>. In particular, the Label Label} objects used * construct the method are no longer valid after this method has been * @param indexes current positions of the instructions to be resized. * instruction must be designated by the index of its <i>last</i> * plus one (or, in other words, by the index of the <i>first</i> byte * the <i>next</i> * @param sizes the number of bytes to be <i>added</i> to the * instructions. More precisely, for i &lt; * <tt>sizes</tt>[i] bytes will be added at the end of the * designated by <tt>indexes</tt>[i] or, if <tt>sizes</tt>[i] * negative, the <i>last</i> |<tt>sizes[i]</tt>| bytes of the * will be removed instruction size <i>must not</i> become * or null). The gaps introduced by this method must be filled * "manually" in the array returned by the #getCode * * @param len the number of instruction to be resized. Must be smaller than * equal to <tt>indexes</tt>.length and * @return the <tt>indexes</tt> array, which now contains the new positions * the resized instructions (designated as */ Modifier protected
